<HEAD>Yet Another Quake Shakes Iranian Town</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small earthquake shook Garmsar early
Sunday, one of more than 150 quakes to hit the northern Iranian town
since August, the official Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
   No casualties or other damage was reported in Sunday's temblor,
which measured 3.5 on the Richter scale, said the agency, monitored
in Nicosia. A quake of that size can cause slight damage.
   The epicenter was registered at Garmsar, 62 miles southeast of
the capital, Tehran, IRNA said.
