<HEAD>Gallery Robbers Steal Two Grandma Moses Painting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two original paintings by Grandma Moses, valued at
$100,000 each, were stolen from a gallery after two men kidnapped
the manager and forced him to unlock the door, police said Sunday.
   Two other original paintings of unknown value were also taken
from the Bloch Gallery.
   The manager, Thomas Waelter, 39, of Medford, was unharmed. He
told police he was kidnapped by two men after a friend dropped him
off in the parking lot of a train station in Medford around 6 p.m.
Saturday.
   Waelter told police the men threw a blanket over him and forced
him in the back of a Sears van. The men drove him to an alley behind
the gallery and then ordered him to go unlock the front door.
   Waelter was tied up with plastic cuffs on his hands and legs
after the men took the paintings and left, police said. Waelter said
he did not recognize the men but they called him by name.
