<HEAD>Kurdistan Province Gives Up Smoking For A Day</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran's Kurdistan province held a
``no-smoking'' day on to encourage tobacco addicts to give up the
habit, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported Sunday.
   The agency, monitored in Nicosia, said smoking was banned in
government offices and public places on Saturday under an agreement
between a local tobacco company and the Physical Training
Organization.
   It said stores stopped selling tobacco products.
   Kurdistan was the third province in the past three months to
organize a ``no-smoking'' day, the agency said.
