<FIRST>r i AM-Peru     01-22 0140</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Peru,0144</SECOND>
<HEAD>Guerrillas Fire Into Crowd, Kill Three</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUANCAYO, PERU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Suspected leftist guerrillas fired into a
crowd on Sunday, killing three people and wounding 15 in this Andean
city, officials said.
   About 1,000 residents of this shantytown were in an outdoor
community meeting with the mayor, Ricardo Bohoquez, when eight
gunmen opened fire on the crowd with pistols and machine guns,
police said.
   Huancayo police said Bohoquez, who was wounded twice in the
chest, was the target of the attack. The assailants also hurled
dynamite during the attack, police said.
   Police blamed members of the Maoist Shining Path guerrilla
movement, which began an insurrection in 1980 in an effort to set up
a Marxist state in Peru. More than 12,000 people have died in the
uprising. Many attacks are aimed at local governent officials in
rural villages.
</TEXT>
