<FIRST>r a AM-NakedMan     01-22 0307</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Naked Man,0314</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nude Man Strolls Through Restaurant, Is Arrested in Fatal Hit-Run</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MALIBU, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A nude man shouting ``Hail Satan'' as he
strolled through a popular beachfront restaurant was arrested and
later linked to a fatal hit-run crash, authorities said Sunday.
   Brian L. Harlow, 28, of Malibu allegedly was driving a stolen
pickup truck involved in the Pacific Coast Highway crash minutes
before the Friday night restaurant escapade that led to his arrest,
said Officer Monte Keifer of the California Highway Patrol.
   Harlow, hospitalized briefly for observation at Harbor-UCLA
Medical Center, was booked for investigation of murder and was being
held without bail Sunday at the Los Angeles County Jail, Keifer said.
   Startled diners at the Chart House restaurant avoided conversing
with the nude man as he ``strolled casually through the restaurant
showing himself to all the tables,'' said manager Greg Butler. He
then sat at an unoccupied table.
   ``A waiter told him he'd better leave and he said he was Satan
and he was going to die. We left him alone, hoping the sheriffs
would show up,'' Butler said. Dozens of customers looked and
giggled, he said.
   Five minutes after entering the restaurant yelling ``Hail
Satan,'' he walked through the crowded bar to an outside patio and
down to a rocky outcropping on the beach, where he was detained by
authorities.
   A pickup Harlow left running in the restaurant parking lot was
involved in a fatal accident Friday at 11:40 p.m. in Corral Canyon,
said CHP Officer Richard Perez. The truck had been reported as
stolen.
   ``The pickup driver hit a motorcycle from behind, rear-ended it,
then kept going,'' the officer said.
   The 22-year-old passenger on the motorcycle, a recently
discharged sailor from Norfolk, Va., was killed. Identification was
withheld until relatives could be contacted. The motorcyclist
suffered minor injuries, Perez said.
</TEXT>
