<FIRST>r f AM-Peru-Oil     01-22 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Peru-Oil,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Peruvian President Announces Major Oil Discovery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Peruvian President Alan Garcia announced a
major oil discovery by Occidental Petroleum Corp. in a jungle area
in Peru.
   The oil deposits, estimated at 600 million barrels, were
discovered in a jungle region called La Collpa in Ucayali, 355 miles
northeast of Lima, Garcia told a news conference Friday, according
to the official gazette El Peruano.
   According to the president's figures, the new deposits will yield
enough oil to make Peru a net oil exporter, and secure enough oil,
energy, fuel and cash to meet the country's development needs for
the next 15 years.
   The total value of the oil at current world prices is $10
billion, Garcia was quoted as saying.
   Occidental began its exploration in the region two months ago,
Garcia said. He did not say when Occidental will begin to pump the
oil.
   Officials of Los Angeles-based Occidental were unavailable for
comment Sunday.
</TEXT>
